               <p>Q. Did you write upon both these notes the first time you went to Mr. Westwood or did you not - A. I am sure I forget.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you remember what your deposition was a quarter of a year ago, that you writ upon them both at one time, or did you not - A. I am sure I cannot rightly say; they were pinned together I know.</p>
               <p>Q. Now, sir, take these notes in your hand, and tell me what time elapsed after you wrote a stranger, and 
