                  </persName>
             - A. I wrote his name on the 22nd, I did not know his name before the 22nd, he gave me direction when we were at the Five Bells.</p>
               <p>Q. Monday was the 19th - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Tuesday you saw him again - A. Yes; Wednesday evening I saw him again, then I gave him some gin.</p>
               <p>Q. Who was you to leave this gin for at this woman's - A. I was not to leave any that present time.</p>
               <p>Q. And now you pretend that you were introduced without knowing what name of the person was. Do you mean that you were introduced to a man's wife without knowing her name, and that his name never passed between you and the officers until that day - A. No.</p>
               <p>Q. How long have you been acquainted with Avory - A. About six or seven months.</p>
               <p>Q. That was after your return from Worcester. Have you got Griffiths direction - A. No; Mr. Westwood had it.</p>
               <p>Q. Who introduced you to Avory - A. Wainwright.</p>
               <p>Q. You told Avory at your first introduction of your unfortunate affair at Worcester - A. No, not when first I was introduced, it was soon after.</p>
               <p>
            
